oking down on them for doing it at other people's expense.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ustormwindthunderpaw.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Stormwind Thunderpaw</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 39<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/8/01 12:59:51 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=164.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Twinks and Powerlevelers.... :-/</span><hr size=1> Kaz I agree and disagree in some points. YES - ppl shouldnt PL in high population places or low mob spot. I have actually been PLing for last 3 Days for 5 different ppl. I encourage the low population or off peak hour hunts of nice zones. Everfrost cannot be beaten for the most low lvl mobs 1-5, the tundra is perfect for 5-8 or so, at 8 - 15 The zone into Permafrost or Invis into a deep reccess of BlackBurrow if at peak time if off peak then Oasis (was 6 ppl in zone all night, we were 4 of em) til 18 if not crowded. We have already done this so far and off To LOIO for 18 - 28, a zone also hugely underpopulated reguardless of time. Once you break 28+ you are a higher lvl than most of the server and have alot of freedom to roam the great exp zones til ye find one that suites your needs. <br><br>As far as the RP police go, I have been accused of being a member but only because of stating my sadness at the lack of RP by most high lvl ppl. Forcing someone to move from a hunting spot is as rude as telling them how to run thier lives or their RP sessions. If PLers are selfish and PLing in high traffic zones its just like if a Druid up and quad kites all the named sisters on Sisters Isle (8 spawns) when a group of 5 ppl is already there hunting. Its a rude thing to do and shows lack of consideration for others and the community. Just jot thier names down and remember them later for their acts and keep grinding forward having fun at your own pace. Reputation is everything here and what stigma's you today can have serious affects later. Many jerks will realize this in time or already have. <br><br>Peace and Love friends! Its a game have fun in it, otherwise why are ye here /chuckle<br>Stormwind <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ugrimwyrd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimwyrd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/8/01 3:30:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=164.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Twinks and Powerlevelers.... :-/</span><hr size=1> I'm sorry Kaz, I sympathize with your frustration, but can't support your arguments.<br><br>You say it hurts everyone in the zone when two are killing the amount of wisps that five would kill. Wrong. It hurts you because you wanted to hunt wisps. You want the wisps (for the same reason they do, experience and loot) and can't have them, so you're mad.<br><br>You imply that the two are being dishonest in their hunting tactics. This seems like a rationalization of your frustration to me. What is so morally reprehensible about a high level pulling monsters to a low level? You've already admitted you have no problem with it, if it's done somewhere where it doesn't interfere with your hunting.<br><br>Your arguments and frustration all keep coming back to the simple fact that you wanted the choice monsters in the choice spot, and couldn't have them.<br><br>I've wanted choice monsters in choice spots and not been able to have them too, that's one of the downsides of playing in a large multiplayer environment. One of the upsides, is that you can get help hunting from your friends/guildmates and get hand-me-downs from your friends/guildmates. You call it dishonest twinking and powerleveling. I call it being social and having fun with friends. Do I get frustrated when other people are in my way? Absolutely. But, I recognize that they have just as much right to enjoy themselves as I do, so I go do something else.<br><br>Oh well, I have a feeling we'll never agree on this subject, since the debate has raged for years. I wish you the best Kaz, and the only reason I argue with you is that I feel if you could let go of your frustration with twinks/PLs it would let you relax and enjoy the game more.<br><br>On the plus side, I often see many wisps in WC with no one hunting them on this server. So maybe the event that ticked you off will not happen very often to you here.<br><br>Grimwyrd<br><br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ugolsec.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Golsec</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 43<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/8/01 4:16:05 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=164.topic&index=17>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.cloudk.clara.net/storage/golavatar.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Twinks and Powerlevelers.... :-/</span><hr size=1> Killing 5 wisps at once when everyone else is trying to hunt them is greedy.  Seems a simple enough concept to me <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>-- <br><img src="http://www.cloudk.clara.net/storage/golsecsig.jpg"><br>(Also known as Cloudien, Druid of The Rathe server)</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ugrimwyrd.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Grimwyrd</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 26<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/8/01 5:03:07 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=164.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Twinks and Powerlevelers.... :-/</span><hr size=1> Aye, it is Golsec. And I wouldn't do it, because I don't like to harshen another persons mellow.<br><br>But, getting bent out of shape cause someone is killing the wisps that YOU want to kill is also basically greedy. It comes back to YOU want the wisps, and you're mad cause someone else is getting them.<br><br>It's real easy to point the finger and say someone else is being rude and greedy, but most people need to look in a mirror and realize that it's greed and envy that are driving their feelings too. People get mad cause they're not getting &quot;their fair share&quot; and pissed that the other person is getting &quot;more than their fair share&quot;. But the whole &quot;fair share&quot; concept is flawed.<br><br>A 30th and 10th level team have just as much right to those wisps as anyone else, and it's greedy and rude to make them go to the ass-end of Kunark just so that they don't get in your way.<br><br>That's the point I'm trying to make. This game is a lot more relaxing when you don't get caught up in what others are doing and just try to have fun. If you are in WC, see a wisp, want to kill a wisp...then, kill it. If there aren't wisps to kill, don't concern yourself with why.<br><br>Maybe a 10th/30th team is hogging them, maybe there are five 12th levels soloing them...it doesn't matter. If there are not enough wisps to keep you happy, then do something else, don't get mad at the other people for ruining your gaming experience.<br><br>The last time I tried to hunt wisps in WC, I wasn't finding very many. This shocked me, because there were only a couple people in the zone. It turned out that a ranger was tracking them down and taking them out. I didn't have tracking, so I couldn't compete with him. Did I get mad at the ranger for hogging the wisps? Did I get mad at him for getting about five kills to my one? No, of course not. I was a little frustrated that I was in the mood to hunt wisps and wasn't able to, but I found something else to do.<br><br>Oh well, like I said. I'm just playing devil's advocate, because I think people let the actions of others bother them too much in this game.<br><br>Cheers,<br>Grimwyrd <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uwangdang.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Wangdang</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/8/01 5:13:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=164.topic&index=19>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Twinks and Powerlevelers.... :-/</span><hr size=1> This Kaz crybaby guy is why I wish there was a RP PvP server.  You could kill him and then he couldn't spam the zone with more crybaby chatter. Sure, he would most likely start spamming you directly, but a simple /ignore crybaby would take care of the problem and others wouldn't be able to hear his rantings.  That is of course unless they were in earshot. Side stepping away until you were out of range would solve that quickly though.<br><br>Oh wait! Then the crybaby would come to the message boards and start crying there! Hmmm, maybe we could have some sort of Message Board PvP rules as well????<br><br>              ---- He who drinks strong brew ---- <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukaz807.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kaz807</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 8<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(12/8/01 9:08:47 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=164.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Twinks and Powerlevelers.... :-/</span><hr size=1> &quot;Your arguments and frustration all keep coming back to the simple fact that you wanted the choice monsters in the choice spot, and couldn't have them.&quot;<br><br>No, it's a supply and demand thing.  There's a certain supply, so many people who want some of it, and two taking way more than their equal share.  I wouldn't have a problem in the world if there were just a lot of people hunting wisps.  It's the people PLing their twinks on wisps that bugs me.<br><br>Does PLing offend me?  No, if it doesn't affect me.  But if it screws me over when some dolt and his drood buddy are PLing right next to the rest of the general population who suddently can't find many pulls, then yeah, it gets on my bad side.<br><br>All these &quot;friends&quot; showing up on FV and being PLed to whatever level they want is what's going to quickly turn this nice quiet server into just another dood filled abomination, just with some extra rules.  I can already see a lot of people liking the whole lack of no-drop thing; and the one char only thing doesn't hurt so much if your buddy is twinking you and PLing you up anyway, right?<br><br>Bah.<br><br>&quot;This Kaz crybaby guy is why I wish there was a RP PvP server.&quot;<br><br>I guarantee you, the guy PLing would be ganged up on by fed up hunters way sooner than he could kill the guy who had the balls to call him an ass to his face. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page  <b>1</b> <a href=http://pub94.e